race.comment: MAGIC SPEED (8) stalked the pace then quickened nicely to record an easy first-up win over 900m at Queanbeyan last time out. Promising filly who looks capable of moving up to this level. TWINKLING STAR (7) won her maiden first-up then came from well back to get up for third here at this trip a fortnight ago. Didn't have much luck last start so the run was full of merit. Major player again. Last start Kembla maiden winner BALLYHOO (6) is yet to prove himself on top of the ground but is back in good order and worth the benefit of the doubt. The 26.0 on offer in early markets is the appeal. EMPRESS OF JAPAN (2) returns after a 24-week spell. Two recent trials should have her forward enough. Has won at this trip before so while 1100m is short of her best she is a chance while fresh. HELL OF A FOX (1) resumes. Came of age after transferring to Luke Pepper last prep, bringing up a hat trick before a failure to close the campaign. In the mix although the big weight is a steadier.
